(41, 'upcoming-events', 'Thoughts from President\'s Desk', '<p>\r\n	Respected Seniors, my Dear Friends and Brothers and Sisters,&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I am thankful to all that you have trusted me to serve my beloved alma mater as President of the Alumni Association.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I am not confident, and I don&rsquo;t want to be that I will be able to guide the association with innovation &amp; vision for success; rather I believe that, until &amp; unless you all perform, it is impossible to lead such a prestigious platform.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I hope, all of you will take an active part with your ideas &amp; activities. The verticals or Subcommittees are formed by the Alumni Association, which can perform successfully only if all of you take active participation in Alumni initiatives.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	I shall remain busy in housekeeping only which is essential to run such an active and growing organization. The decision will be a process of harnessing with participation from all of you (starting from the governing body to vertical members, senior alumni who guide us as mentors, members of the alumni association and every alumnus of our beloved alma mater). We will respect the guidance of our respected Principal Sir, our professors and be humble to all of the stakeholders related to our beautiful alma mater.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our motto should be to accept new ideas having relevance to the present scenario &amp; future vision as</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	well. I hope you all will be honestly expressive about your problem, before taking any responsibility and guide future generation accordingly.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Yours Faithfully,</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Gautam Bhaduri</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	26-09-2020</p>\r\n', 'admin', '2020-09-26 13:07:30', 1);
